column5: Heading to Gull Rock July 19. Wondering how fishing has been recently.
I was out yesterday for a couple hours, picked up 1 or 2 in several sites. The bite has slowed down due to the may fly hatch but that is over now and it should pick up by the time you get here.
I heard tonight that one of the neighbours talked to a guy at the golf course who caught a 29 inch walleye in Keg Lake. That is the biggest I've heard of in the Gullrock area.
